# Tech stack

- TypeScript (strict) + React 19 + Vite.
- Tailwind CSS v4 via `@tailwindcss/vite` (CSS-first `@theme`, not a JS config).
- shadcn/ui (`new-york`) primitives; `lucide-react` icons; `sonner` toasts.
- State + persistence: Zustand with the `persist` middleware -> `localStorage` (versioned key).
- Animation: `motion` (Framer Motion); celebrations: `canvas-confetti`.
- Dates: `date-fns`. PWA: `vite-plugin-pwa` + `@vite-pwa/assets-generator`.

## Layout

- `src/lib/gamification.ts` — pure XP/level/streak/achievement logic (no React/store imports).
- `src/store/useHabitStore.ts` — Zustand store + persist.
- `src/components/ui/` — shadcn primitives; feature components alongside.
- `src/types.ts` — shared types.

## Rules

- Keep business/gamification logic in `lib/` pure functions, not in components.
- Do NOT add a backend, server, or database.
- Prefer zero new dependencies; any addition must be free and static-host compatible.
- Full details: `docs/ai/architecture.md`.
